- element
    - physical
    - heat
    - nature
    - cryo
    - electric
- arts infliction
    - heat infliction
    - nature infliction
    - cryo infliction
    - electric infliction
- physical infliction
    - vulnerable
- infliction refers to all arts and physical inflictions
- arts reaction
    - combustion = any arts infliction + heat infliction
    - corrosion = any arts infliction + nature infliction
    - solidification = any arts infliction + cryo infliction
    - electrification = any arts infliction + electric infliction
- physical reaction
    - [ignore] lifted = vulnerable + lift
    - [ignore] knocked down = vulnerable + knock down
    - breached = vulnerable + breach
    - crushed = vulnerable + crush
- reaction refers to all arts reaction and physical interactions resulting in a physical status
- status level
    - inflictions have status levels (aka stacks) ranging from 0-4 (0 means a lack of infliction), the status level will transfer during a reaction
    - reactions have status levels ranging from 1-4, with higher levels offering enhanced effects/multipliers
- gauge
    - enemy stagger meter
    - ultimate energy meter
- resource: a gauge that often has regeneration properties
    - skill points
    - [ignore] stamina
- trigger condition
    - some events can only be activated when certain interactions occur, such as:
        - some operator attacks require certain reactions to occur
- combat skill types
    - basic attack
        - basic attack: event with multiple segments each containing multiple frames
        - final strike: last frame of last segment in basic attack event is categorized as final strike
            - restores SP
            - builds stagger
        - finisher: event that can be activated with enemy stagger as trigger condition
            - restores SP
    - basic skill: event activated by expending SP
    - combo skill: event activated by meeting trigger condition(s)
    - ultimate skill: event activated by expending ultimate gauge
